The paper deals with spoken term detection (STD) using an end-to-end model based on attention-based multi-hop networks. The model can be trained in a supervised or unsupervised manner. The paper involves speech processing, natural language processing, and machine learning, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the use of attention mechanisms and multi-hop networks suggests a focus on deep learning, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
